# CODEOWNERS — mandatory review for fleet's security-load-bearing code.
#
# Most of fleet is fine to review like any other change. A handful of paths,
# however, encode the non-negotiable invariants the whole project rests on (see
# AGENTS.md "Non-negotiable invariants"): the rootless-Podman sandbox, the
# governance/policy core, the host-side credential boundary, the authn/z layer,
# the irreversible database migrations, and the CI gates themselves. A quiet
# weakening of any of these — by a future contributor or by an auto-merging
# agent — would be a security regression even if every test still passed.
#
# This file routes those paths to a required reviewer. GitHub uses the LAST
# matching pattern for a given file, so the more specific security rules below
# override the catch-all at the top. CODEOWNERS only REQUESTS review by itself;
# it becomes a hard gate when branch protection on `main` enables "Require
# review from Code Owners" (see the recommended ruleset below).
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recommended branch-protection ruleset for `main` (set in repo Settings →
# Branches/Rules; requires admin, so it is a documented manual follow-up — this
# PR only adds the CODEOWNERS file). CONTRIBUTING.md notes the same:
#   - Require a pull request before merging.
#   - Require approvals: >= 1.
#   - Require review from Code Owners.            <-- makes the rules below binding
#   - Dismiss stale approvals on new commits.
#   - Require status checks to pass (the full CI gate: Go build/vet/lint/test,
#     the -race lane, govulncheck, web lint/test/build, Playwright mocked+live,
#     and gitleaks) and require branches to be up to date.
#   - Do NOT allow bypassing the above (no force-push / no admin override).
#
# Dependabot auto-merge interaction: .github/workflows/auto-merge-dependabot.yml
# only enables `gh pr merge --auto` on PATCH-level dependency bumps, so GitHub
# still holds the merge until every required status check passes. It does NOT
# bypass branch protection or Code Owner review: a Dependabot PR that touches a
# CODEOWNERS-matched, non-dependency path (e.g. a workflow, a migration, the
# sandbox) is still gated on the required code-owner approval below. Routine
# manifest/lockfile bumps live outside these paths and merge on green CI.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Catch-all: every file has an owner so nothing is silently unowned. Specific
# rules below take precedence for the security-sensitive paths.
*                                       @bradflaugher

# Sandbox hardening — every agent tool call runs inside this rootless-Podman
# sandbox; there is no fast path that skips it.
/internal/sandbox/                      @bradflaugher
/config/default/sandbox/                @bradflaugher

# Governance + policy core (the single governed run loop, Gate-3, the MCP
# credential allowlist). New entrypoints must adapt I/O around this, not fork a
# second, weaker governance path.
/internal/agentcore/policy.go               @bradflaugher
/internal/agentcore/agent_policy.go         @bradflaugher
/internal/agentcore/credential_allowlist.go @bradflaugher
/internal/agentcore/mcp_broker.go           @bradflaugher

# Credential boundary — MCP/connector secrets are brokered host-side and never
# enter the sandbox, the agent container, the model context, or logs.
/internal/creds/                        @bradflaugher
/internal/mcpbroker/                    @bradflaugher

# Authentication / authorization and rate limiting (HTTP API).
/internal/httpapi/auth.go               @bradflaugher
/internal/httpapi/auth_verify.go        @bradflaugher
/internal/httpapi/ratelimit.go          @bradflaugher

# Irreversible schema changes. The chat and scheduler migration systems are
# separate; both apply forward-only.
/internal/store/migrations/             @bradflaugher
/internal/sched/db/migrations/          @bradflaugher

# CI gates and dependency/agent automation — these workflows ARE the merge
# guarantees, including the Dependabot auto-merge path.
/.github/workflows/                     @bradflaugher
/.github/dependabot.yml                 @bradflaugher
/.github/CODEOWNERS                     @bradflaugher
